
-----------
- To quickly run:

0. SetupProject Gaudi ROOT (if at Cern)

1. modify tag.opts to point to the ntuple or ntuple 
   directory that you want to use.

2. type "make" 

3. have fun :)

By default the program will pick up the test ntuple:
/afs/cern.ch/user/m/mgrabalo/public/analysis.root
This was produced by:
gaudirun.py $FLAVOURTAGGINGCHECKEROPTS/DVBTaggingAnalysis.py

You can find documentation about this program at
https://cern.ch/musy/tagging

and about tagging in general at:
https://twiki.cern.ch/twiki/bin/viewauth/LHCb/FlavourTagging
